In Atom Version 0.175.0 (0.175.0) Mac OSX
language-javascript version 0.55.0

The following when placed in a javascript file should be legal but breaks syntax highlighting:

``` javascript
// Regex from http://blog.stevenlevithan.com/archives/parseuri
var myobj = {
  strict: /^(?:([^:\/?#]+):)?(?:\/\/((?:(([^:@]*)(?::([^:@]*))?)?@)?([^:\/?#]*)(?::(\d*))?))?((((?:[^?#\/]*\/)*)([^?#]*))(?:\?([^#]*))?(?:#(.*))?)/,
};
console.log('This is all yellow.');
// And so is this!
```

![screen shot 2015-01-25 at 11 17 05 am](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/1256409/5889590/c21c94f6-a483-11e4-88ac-ee444dcc3ee0.png)

This also does a similar thing:

``` javascript
// Regex from http://blog.stevenlevithan.com/archives/parseuri
var myobj = {
  loose:  /^(?:(?![^:@]+:[^:@\/]*@)([^:\/?#.]+):)?(?:\/\/)?((?:(([^:@]*)(?::([^:@]*))?)?@)?([^:\/?#]*)(?::(\d*))?)(((\/(?:[^?#](?![^?#\/]*\.[^?#\/.]+(?:[?#]|$)))*\/?)?([^?#\/]*))(?:\?([^#]*))?(?:#(.*))?)/
};
console.log('This is all green/blue.');
```

![screen shot 2015-01-25 at 11 19 36 am](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/1256409/5889602/6d19af9c-a484-11e4-9208-5a9f3b022c89.png)

_(I am able to reproduce this in safe mode in latest Atom 0.175.0)_

Not always, but quiet often, I have partial selection left behind when I select a portion of code on one line and then start typing hoping to replace the selected chars. When I type my first char, this causes selection jump to the characters on the right and they get deleted when I type the second char. For example, I have this `test.js` file:

``` js
  var where = _.pick({
    classified_id: query.classId,
    section_id: query.secId,
    category_id: query.catId
  }, function(val, key) {
    console.log('  **** val:', val);
    console.log('  **** key:', key);
    return !_.isUndefined(val);
  });
```

To replicate:
1. Select a portion of code on any line with a mouse or a touchpad. Release the mouse button.
1.  Switch to keyboard and press the space bar
1. You should see that the selected chars were deleted, but some of the chars on the right are selected now too. 
1. Press space bar again, and those extra selected chars get deleted
1. Do steps 1 and 2 a few times if you can't replicate it on first time.

This is a real pain since I always have to do `Command + Z` to undo  these side effects. Sometimes, I don't notice it and my code no longer runs.
